  ],
  "remarks": "LLC Molot Arms, founded in 2011 in Moscow, is a Russian defence manufacturer engaged in the production of firearms and unmanned aerial systems (UAVs). Its flagship product is the “Zhmil-17” first-person view (FPV) combat UAV, manufactured in Kirov Oblast since 2023 and supplied to Russian forces in Ukraine. The company’s current monthly output exceeds 500 UAV units, with State-backed plans to increase to 1 000 UAVs per month in 2025.",
